jobs.description:
Providing technical advice on transactions, reviewing relevant contracts and documentation;
Indirect Tax advisor to the franchisee network and to a diverse range of Joint Venture investments;
Identifying, managing and providing solutions to emerging indirect tax issues due to legislative or business changes and developing suitable educational support to implement changes;
Advising on GST aspects of SAP implementation in specific functions, e.g. rebates;
Managing GST, PAYG, Payroll Tax, Income Tax Instalment, withholding tax, and FBT Compliance for all Harvey Norman Group entities;
Supporting the financial reporting team and tax and treasury areas of the business;
Liaising with the ATO to resolve any issues or audit matters;
Managing the Indirect Tax Function in line with Harvey Norman’s Tax Framework, reviewing and monitoring procedures, performance and policies. 
Managing and developing two team members within the Indirect Tax Function.

Providing structuring advice and transaction support to clients, working as part of a team to provide tax and legal advice;
Reviewing contracts for a wide-range of clients, providing indirect tax advice within short time frames
Providing advice in relation to GST, customs duties, WET, FTC and no ABN withholding.

Advising on major acquisitions, disposals and restructuring of businesses (due diligence, contract review and structuring advice);
Advising on cross-border arrangements and co-ordinating multi-jurisdiction advice;
Advising clients across a broad range of industry sectors including finance, mining, retail, technology, aviation, automotive, private equity, charities and not-for-profits;
Involved in lobbying for GST law changes, representing transport industry bodies with the ATO/Treasury;
Obtaining private binding rulings from the ATO;
Implementing input tax credit apportionment methodologies;
Undertaking GST compliance reviews looking at systems and processes employed by clients; 
Successfully negotiating the closure of a number of audits with no action from the ATO;
Involvement in delivering GST training;
Coaching junior staff and undertaking performance reviews.
Providing BAS compliance support to clients;

Advising on major acquisitions, disposals and restructuring of businesses;
Advising on cross-border arrangements and co-ordinating multi-jurisdiction advice;
Involved in lobbying for GST law changes, representing transport industry bodies with the ATO/Treasury;
Involved in successful lobbying of the Finanzamt in Germany to accept that reciprocity exists between Australia and Germany in relation to GST refunds for non-resident businesses;
Advising property clients in relation to the margin scheme and successfully negotiating the closure of a number of audits with no action from the ATO. 
Assisting the Property Council of Australia with responses to various consultations;
Undertaking GST compliance reviews looking at systems and processes employed by clients;
Training Manager – organising internal weekly GST training schedule and delivering training;
Speaking at Indirect Tax Forums and participating in a GST Discussion Group;
Coaching junior staff and undertaking performance reviews.

Advising on major acquisitions, disposals and restructuring of businesses – working in large cross- service line/multi-jurisdictional teams on highly technical complex deals in a high pressure environment to deliver pro-active, integrated advice to client-driven timetables;
Implementing planning arrangements for clients, including risk reviews, disclosure and negotiation with HMRC;
Speaker at specialist tax and industry events, writing articles/chapters in industry magazines and specialist VAT publications;
Delivering VAT and accounting training to HMRC trainee VAT audit officers;
Providing VAT advice on two of the three largest single property acquisitions in the UK;
Sub-group head with responsibility for the day-to-day management of a team of 13 – monitoring staffing levels, utilisation, billing and other KPIs,mentoring and appraising members of the team;
Responsible for developing a professional education strategy for Deloitte’s UK Indirect Tax Team on a National basis which saw first time pass rates for CTA rise from 0% to 71% in two years;
National Co-ordinator of Deloitte’s UK Indirect Tax High Performance Culture Strategy with responsibility for rolling out initiatives on feedback processes, recruitment and alternative rewards;
Secondment to the London Organising Committee of the Olympic Games to deliver a key area of Deloitte’s sponsorship of the 2012 Olympic Games (non-tax role).

The Social Development Internship involved attending the UNHCR NGO Consultations in Geneva.

Other key responsibilities were;
- Preparing briefing reports on social development, human rights and refugee issues;
- Documenting refugee and asylum seeker community consultations;
- Supporting community representatives are the UNHCR NGO consultations in Geneva;
- Advocacy training;
- Attending the Refugee Council of Australia International Policy Network meetings;
- Participation at Australian Asylum Seeker round table at the UNHCR;

Promoted to a senior advocacy and change leadership role, I defined and implemented a disruptive advocacy program across the OPP, Victoria’s largest prosecution legal practice. Forging relationships across the judicial system, I challenged an established culture to enable skilled solicitor advocates to undertake more complex work on behalf of the DPP, driving excellence and efficiency in prosecution services to improve community outcomes and more readily meet the needs of victims. In addition, I managed >20 in-house advocates, overseeing all in-house solicitor advocate prosecutions on indicatable criminal matters across Magistrate, Coroner, County and Supreme Courts while appearing as the lead solicitor advocate in many complex prosecution hearings.

•	Improved solicitor-advocate performance, designing a briefing, training and performance management program driving clear accountabilities;
•	Returned to Specialist Sex Offences Unit to recover and deliver the launch of the Sexual Offences Interactive Legal Education Project in April 2012;
•	As a result of the above, delivered an award-winning skills and cultural change program which included an avatar based cross-examination simulation program, an early AI initiative providing a behavioural benchmark for barristers and advocates cross-examining children in sexual offence cases

Luke leads the data and analytics product strategy and delivery across AGL's Customer Experience transformation program. This includes;

The management of internal and customer facing data products across the Service Design & Delivery Framework (SDDF);

Day-to-day leadership of Data Product Owners whom are creating the building blocks for AGL's next best action and customer personalisation strategies;

Acting as the business partner to business units across Digital Strategy and Operations, Sales & Marketing, Customer Operations and Energy Trading; and

Influencing AGL's big-data and cloud data platform strategies based on the data and analytical needs of the the end customer and/or business unit.

•	Lead 44 staff: Transformation, Project delivery, Customer risk, Insights & Reporting, IVR, Change Management
•	Responsible for driving business planning, championing transformation and business improvement programs to increase core customer KPIs whilst reducing costs;
•	Evaluate and define operating models for future-state success, leading a number of divisional transformations and implementations to align functional delivery with strategic objectives;
•	Drive $152M P&L performance, uplifting through organisational ‘right sizing’, and a suite of projects focused on business improvement, contract review and people development;
•	Project delivery of key Foxtel products: Foxtel broadband, NBN, IQ3 set top box

